# Cursor Rules for TeamHero CLI

Architecture guardrails
• Use ports-and-adapters. Define RepoProvider, SelectionUI, and ReportRunner interfaces in the core.  
• The CLI entry composes adapters and calls a single core orchestration function.  
• No side effects in core. File IO, logging, process env, and child processes live at the edges.

Interactive policy
• The Go TUI (tui/) is the primary interactive frontend. Headless mode is used in CI and pipes.
• Never block on prompts in non-interactive contexts.

Vendoring policy
• The Go TUI resolves its own binary at build time. Provide an env to force headless locally.

Contracts and flags
• Preserve existing flags and output. Add --repos for CSV input and --no-confirm to skip confirmation.  
• Default path favors "all repos" when non-interactive or when the user accepts defaults.

Testing
• Core unit tests use fakes.  
• CI runs headless integration with --repos.  
• Optional smoke test for the TUI is allowed behind a flag and is not required in CI.

Code style
• Small files, single responsibility.
• Pure functions in core, thin adapters, explicit error messages.

AI Generation Policy
• When using generative AI to write code or generate content, never implement fallback behaviors that would allow the system to continue with degraded functionality.
• If AI generation fails, the entire operation must fail with a clear error message rather than falling back to alternative approaches.
• No silent fallbacks are permitted under any circumstances when AI-generated content is involved.

